The simple form of this algorithm avoids the calculation of bond angles, and directs the juxtaposition of the two half-cystines so that the disulfide bond forms with the experimental bond length, bond angles, and SS torsion angle.
In using this algorithm, the energies of eq 14 and 15 are added to the total energy of section VE, and this new total is minimized.
Addendum
When these potential functions were applied to the cis and trans peptide conformations of several model compounds, and the librational entropy included in the free energy, the trans conformation was found to be much more stable than the cis for both nonproline and proline residues, but less so for proline.154 For example, the probabilities of formation of the cis conformation were 8.5 X 10~7 and 4.1 X 10~2 for the N-acetyl-N'-methylamides of GlyGly and Gly-Pro, respectively.154
